1
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:09,280
You're not uncomfortable
if Mink stays here, right?

2
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:11,640
<i>Pun's bedroom is just around the corner.</i>

3
00:02:11,720 --> 00:02:13,320
If you want to sneak over
and see him, feel free.

4
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:15,600
You're clearly not into the five precepts.

5
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:17,720
But I'm the designer.

6
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:19,920
I want to understand
why the client is requesting

7
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:22,240
such drastic changes.

8
00:02:22,320 --> 00:02:24,440
Let's call it. You don't
have to work on this anymore.

9
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:25,600
That's it.

10
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:27,480
The person I used to date is…

11
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:28,680
Win.

12
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:31,760
You're so selfish.

13
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:34,080
Everyone knows who you really are now.

14
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:37,760
Yeah.

15
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:41,160
I've been letting it go,
but don't push me to lose my patience.

16
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:45,320
CERTIFICATE OF MARRIAGE

17
00:03:14,560 --> 00:03:16,680
Why are you greeting your husband
with a face like that?

18
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:25,160
Pun.

19
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:28,040
Let's not waste any more time on this.

20
00:03:29,320 --> 00:03:30,920
Let's just talk honestly.

21
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:36,320
Honestly?

22
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:41,920
I understand why you're laughing.

23
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:45,800
Because I haven't been honest
with you before.

24
00:03:47,840 --> 00:03:51,360
You probably don't trust me anymore,
and I take full responsibility.

25
00:03:53,480 --> 00:03:56,960
I know you probably can't forgive me.

26
00:03:58,360 --> 00:04:00,360
But if we keep this up, it'll just hurt.

27
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:02,360
Let's not force it anymore.

28
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:16,640
Let's get a divorce.

29
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:29,600
Let's part on good terms.

30
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:33,520
So you can find someone
who's better for you.

31
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:41,640
I've already prepared the documents.

32
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,360
You just need to sign.

33
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:47,560
Everything will be over.

34
00:04:54,440 --> 00:04:55,720
It's too easy.

35
00:05:02,280 --> 00:05:03,400
I will get a divorce.

36
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:05,520
But not right now.

37
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:08,160
Our story isn't finished yet.

38
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:11,760
What are you going to do?

39
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,320
I've been talking to my lawyer.

40
00:05:21,080 --> 00:05:23,040
I never intended to go this route.

41
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:27,920
But in my life, I've never been a fool.

42
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:31,960
I've never been tricked
or taken advantage of.

43
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:35,240
Even with my subordinates,
I wouldn't tolerate it.

44
00:05:35,840 --> 00:05:36,760
But my wife,

45
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:40,800
the one I love and trust, is doing this.

46
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:43,920
I won't let it end so easily.

47
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:49,800
You have secrets you haven't told me.

48
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,680
I have things I haven't told you either.

49
00:05:58,520 --> 00:05:59,720
Just wait and see.

50
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,320
Hello.

51
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:33,400
Are you Mrs. Tubtim Attwijit?

52
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:37,040
Yes, that's me. Is there something wrong?

53
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:39,280
I'm Kitti Mekaphet.

54
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:41,520
I'm the lawyer for Mr. Parit Pitthakorn.

55
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:43,560
Mr. Pun?

56
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:46,320
Is this Pun's lawyer?

57
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:51,800
Yes, I've been authorized by Mr. Pun
to handle the debt collection

58
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:54,280
regarding the house you mortgaged.

59
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:56,040
The amount is eight million baht,

60
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:59,720
and you've defaulted on the loan
for two years now.

61
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:03,120
If the debt isn't paid within 60 days,

62
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:06,320
Mr. Pun has instructed me
to proceed with legal action.

63
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:09,440
I will file a lawsuit
and request the court to order

64
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:11,320
the sale of the house at auction.

65
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:13,080
The proceeds will go toward
paying off the debt.

66
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:15,840
The house at auction?

67
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:18,440
Ma'am, where are we supposed to live then?

68
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:21,600
You're lying.

69
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:24,680
Pun is my son-in-law. How could he sue me?

70
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:26,200
Are you a fraud?

71
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:28,040
Here's my business card.

72
00:07:28,640 --> 00:07:32,160
And here are all the documents
with the full details.

73
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:35,760
Please read them carefully
and sign to acknowledge receipt.

74
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:51,320
Why didn't you tell me
you mortgaged the house with Pun?

75
00:07:51,400 --> 00:07:54,240
I didn't want you to worry,
so I didn't tell you.

76
00:07:56,640 --> 00:07:57,960
Since when?

77
00:07:58,040 --> 00:08:01,440
Remember when I mentioned going
on a Macau tour with my friends?

78
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:02,720
And then?

79
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,760
There's a casino there.

80
00:08:04,840 --> 00:08:06,120
I might have gotten a little carried away.

81
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:07,320
Mom!

82
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:10,800
Pie, at first, I was winning millions,

83
00:08:10,880 --> 00:08:12,640
but then I started losing.

84
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:16,720
I tried to win it back, so I borrowed
money from friends to keep playing.

85
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:20,360
But then it all went downhill.
I ended up losing tens of millions.

86
00:08:21,560 --> 00:08:24,760
So, I mortgaged the house with Pun

87
00:08:24,840 --> 00:08:26,600
to get money to pay back my friends.

88
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:30,080
He agreed because I promised him
that I would stop gambling.

89
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:32,080
Mom, why didn't you pay him back?

90
00:08:32,159 --> 00:08:34,880
Pie, who pays back a son-in-law's debt?

91
00:08:34,960 --> 00:08:36,440
Mom!

92
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:39,240
Pie, now's not the time for this!

93
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:43,760
If it wasn't for that incident with Win,
he would've let this debt go.

94
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:46,640
He wouldn't be chasing me for money.

95
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:48,400
He's worth hundreds of millions.

96
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:51,240
Eight million doesn't even matter to him.

97
00:08:58,080 --> 00:09:00,080
Alright, okay.

98
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:02,000
I get it now,

99
00:09:02,680 --> 00:09:06,240
what he meant when he said
our story isn't over.

100
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:09,400
This is the part I didn't know.

101
00:09:09,480 --> 00:09:11,520
And he's using this to get back at me.

102
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:14,680
What? Get back at you?

103
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:19,080
I knew it.

104
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:22,760
First, he cut off my money,
now he wants to take the house.

105
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:26,440
Oh, so he is holding a grudge over this.

106
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:31,040
Pie, I won't let it end like this.

107
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:33,240
I won't let them take the house.

108
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:37,640
You need to go apologize to him
and make him forgive you.

109
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:41,720
Go tell him that being with Win
was a mistake.

110
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:43,600
You didn't want it to end this way.

111
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:46,480
And the reason you hid it from him
is because you were embarrassed.

112
00:09:46,560 --> 00:09:48,560
- Tell him everything, Pie.
- Mom!

113
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:52,280
I've already talked to Pun
about everything.

114
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:53,760
It's over now.

115
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:56,680
But I won't let it end!

116
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:03,160
I won't let Win's issue
ruin things between you and Pun.

117
00:10:03,880 --> 00:10:06,360
You have to make up with him right now.

118
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:09,960
Do whatever it takes to make him
the good person he was before.

119
00:10:10,880 --> 00:10:14,680
We've fought through everything together
to get where we are today.

120
00:10:14,760 --> 00:10:18,920
Please don't let what happened with Win
destroy everything.

121
00:10:34,560 --> 00:10:35,760
I knew it!

122
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:38,280
There had to be something for sure.

123
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:39,440
Her mother is something else.

124
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:42,000
She had the nerve to say her daughter

125
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:44,280
is innocent, pure,
and has never had a boyfriend.

126
00:10:44,920 --> 00:10:46,720
Pun was her first.

127
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:48,160
She was lying through her teeth.

128
00:10:48,760 --> 00:10:52,040
This is the issue that's causing problems
between Pun and Pie.

129
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:53,280
No wonder.

130
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:55,160
That's why he ended up back at the house.

131
00:10:55,720 --> 00:10:57,800
He must have been tricked
by his wife and brother.

132
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:00,880
See? She's not a good person.

133
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:03,040
She probably convinced Win
to hide it from Pun.

134
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:04,920
She's awful, really awful.

135
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:07,120
Don't jump to conclusions.

136
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:09,240
They just used to date.

137
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:10,960
It's not a big deal.

138
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:14,000
Yeah, it wouldn't be a big deal
if they weren't lying.

139
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:17,080
But this is intentional deception,
trying to trick our son.

140
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:20,480
Who knows, with Win coming back,

141
00:11:20,560 --> 00:11:23,040
the old sparks might reignite.

142
00:11:23,120 --> 00:11:24,560
No wonder Pun is so angry.

143
00:11:24,640 --> 00:11:26,480
But this is deliberate manipulation.

144
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:30,400
This kind of malicious thinking
must've come from her mother.

145
00:11:30,480 --> 00:11:31,680
That's right!

146
00:11:31,760 --> 00:11:35,800
After all these years, you should've seen
that Pie is a soft-hearted person.

147
00:11:35,880 --> 00:11:37,920
You shouldn't be angry with her.

148
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:39,320
She's a pitiful person.

149
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:40,600
She's pretending!

150
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:43,160
Pie is an adult now.

151
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:45,560
If she wanted to tell the truth,
she could.

152
00:11:45,640 --> 00:11:47,320
Her mother didn't lock her mouth.

153
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:50,320
When practicing Dharma,
didn't you learn the five precepts?

154
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:51,880
The monks teach us not to lie,

155
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:53,880
and yet you're siding
with someone who's lying.

156
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:58,400
But monks also teach us
to have compassion for others.

157
00:11:58,480 --> 00:12:00,440
I have no compassion for bad people.

158
00:12:00,520 --> 00:12:01,960
Suit yourself.

159
00:12:02,040 --> 00:12:04,240
I'm going to find a peaceful place

160
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:06,600
to meditate and send out some goodwill.

161
00:12:07,920 --> 00:12:09,000
Hey, Sil!

162
00:12:09,680 --> 00:12:11,760
Don't send any goodwill
to Pie and her mother.

163
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:13,000
It’s a waste!

164
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:25,680
Pun isn't answering the phone?

165
00:12:27,760 --> 00:12:30,200
He hung up on me.
He probably doesn't want to talk.

166
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:33,880
Mom.

167
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:36,520
How about we find a way to pay him back?

168
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:39,120
I've saved up some money,
and you can sell everything you have.

169
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:41,280
The house and the car,
just get rid of them.

170
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:43,680
Then we can buy a small house,
just enough for us to live in.

171
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:46,000
No, we're not selling.

172
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:48,120
I won't let go of this house.

173
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:51,200
This debt happened because Pun is angry.

174
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:53,080
We need to make him stop being angry.

175
00:12:53,160 --> 00:12:55,440
I'll try to talk to him myself.

176
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:18,760
PIE'S MOM

177
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:28,520
What's up, Mom?

178
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:30,720
You know why I'm calling, Pun.

179
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:35,200
Do you realize how shocked I was
when you sent a lawyer?

180
00:13:35,960 --> 00:13:39,040
Once you're no longer shocked,
you can discuss the debt with my lawyer.

181
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:40,120
<i>Oh no, Pun.</i>

182
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:43,320
You know I don't have anything.
Can you please not do this to me?

183
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:47,160
<i>Pun, I know you're really angry,</i>

184
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:49,560
<i>but please don't take</i>
<i>your anger out on me.</i>

185
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:52,000
The issue with Pie lying to you
and hiding things from you

186
00:13:52,080 --> 00:13:54,360
and the debt on the house
are two separate matters.

187
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:56,080
I want you to see that, Pun.

188
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:58,360
You should separate things too, Mom.

189
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:01,080
<i>The issue between Pie and me is one thing.</i>

190
00:14:01,160 --> 00:14:04,200
But you owe money,
and you need to pay it back.

191
00:14:04,280 --> 00:14:06,400
Even if Pie and I
have a normal relationship,

192
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:08,000
you still have to pay your debt.

193
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:11,280
Pun, have some pity on me.

194
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:13,680
We're family, you know.

195
00:14:15,560 --> 00:14:18,360
Family doesn't lie, hide things,
or deceive each other.

196
00:14:19,160 --> 00:14:21,640
I don't want a fake family like yours.

197
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:26,000
Right now, we're only talking
as creditor and debtor.

198
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:29,280
Pun, I'm sorry. I was wrong.

199
00:14:29,360 --> 00:14:31,280
<i>Please forgive me.</i>

200
00:14:31,360 --> 00:14:33,360
<i>Please, Pun. I promise</i>

201
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:36,280
I won't lie or hide anything
from you again.

202
00:14:36,880 --> 00:14:38,600
<i>You can have me swear</i>

203
00:14:38,680 --> 00:14:40,640
or apologize to you in person.

204
00:14:40,720 --> 00:14:43,320
Please, Pun, I truly am sorry.

205
00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:45,000
Five years.

206
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:46,640
Huh?

207
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:48,960
I've known Pie for five years.

208
00:14:50,280 --> 00:14:52,920
You've had five years
to tell me the truth.

209
00:14:53,640 --> 00:14:55,440
<i>But you chose to lie.</i>

210
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:59,080
I have the right to demand my money back.

211
00:14:59,680 --> 00:15:00,560
<i>That's it.</i>

212
00:15:01,800 --> 00:15:03,320
I don't have time to talk to a debtor.

213
00:15:04,280 --> 00:15:06,240
If you want to talk,
you can speak to my lawyer.

214
00:15:07,280 --> 00:15:09,800
Wait, Pun! Pun!

215
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:32,640
Mom.

216
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:39,880
Rok?

217
00:15:46,760 --> 00:15:47,920
- Hey.
- Hey.

218
00:15:50,280 --> 00:15:52,560
- You go first.
- You speak first.

219
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:53,680
You go first.

220
00:15:53,760 --> 00:15:55,400
I told you to speak first.

221
00:16:01,680 --> 00:16:02,640
Okay.

222
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:10,920
I'm sorry…

223
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:14,720
for never telling you about Win.

224
00:16:17,880 --> 00:16:20,160
Can you tell me straight up why?

225
00:16:21,160 --> 00:16:22,880
What were you thinking?

226
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:24,800
What's your reasoning, Pie?

227
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:31,960
Well…

228
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:00,960
When I was with Win…

229
00:17:09,480 --> 00:17:10,839
I was pregnant.

230
00:17:17,560 --> 00:17:19,280
I didn't know.

231
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:24,560
Do you remember
when we went to the boxing gym?

232
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:28,880
I remember.

233
00:17:31,120 --> 00:17:32,160
I…

234
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:39,120
I miscarried.

235
00:17:47,560 --> 00:17:48,680
Pie.

236
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:54,680
I…

237
00:17:55,320 --> 00:17:57,480
I felt horrible.

238
00:18:00,720 --> 00:18:03,200
You know how much my mom had hopes for me.

239
00:18:04,440 --> 00:18:07,200
I wasn't just carrying
my own disappointment.

240
00:18:07,280 --> 00:18:09,760
I was carrying
my mom's disappointment too.

241
00:18:11,640 --> 00:18:13,360
I understand you. I get it.

242
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:19,160
My whole life, I've only had my mom.

243
00:18:21,320 --> 00:18:23,080
When I hurt her…

244
00:18:25,320 --> 00:18:27,840
it felt like the greatest sin.

245
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:33,080
I wanted to fix everything,
to make her happy.

246
00:18:38,960 --> 00:18:40,920
And then Pun came into the picture.

247
00:18:44,960 --> 00:18:45,800
Let me tell you.

248
00:18:45,880 --> 00:18:49,680
At that moment,
whatever my mom told me to do, I did it.

249
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:53,480
Since I was a kid,

250
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,960
I've seen my mom cry
because of disappointment.

251
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:00,920
I…

252
00:19:10,640 --> 00:19:14,360
I didn't want to see her cry
from disappointment again.

253
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:19,080
I was willing to do anything
to make her happy.

254
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:24,600
That included hiding the past.

255
00:19:26,920 --> 00:19:29,000
Burying and suppressing it,

256
00:19:29,840 --> 00:19:30,920
never bringing it up again.

257
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:36,080
Then why are you bringing it up now?

258
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:40,440
Is it because Win came back?

259
00:19:44,360 --> 00:19:45,320
No.

260
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:53,800
I told the truth

261
00:19:55,680 --> 00:19:57,360
because I've learned that…

262
00:20:00,080 --> 00:20:03,200
true love shouldn't begin with secrets

263
00:20:06,040 --> 00:20:06,960
Rok.

264
00:20:07,520 --> 00:20:10,200
Pun doesn't really know who I am.

265
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:14,200
And I feel terrible
that I kept secrets from him.

266
00:20:15,720 --> 00:20:18,080
So, I decided to tell him
the truth about everything.

267
00:20:19,520 --> 00:20:21,480
Including the miscarriage too?

268
00:20:35,960 --> 00:20:36,960
I get it now.

269
00:20:37,640 --> 00:20:39,680
That explains why Pun
went after Win so hard.

270
00:20:40,720 --> 00:20:43,000
Everyone knows he really wants kids.

271
00:20:43,680 --> 00:20:44,760
And I think…

272
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:49,600
This is even worse
than you being Win's ex.

273
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:51,960
Now Pun had Mink stay at his house.

274
00:20:52,720 --> 00:20:54,480
He's definitely going to get back at you.

275
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:05,120
If he wants to make me suffer,

276
00:21:07,120 --> 00:21:08,400
I'm ready to take it.

277
00:21:12,640 --> 00:21:14,120
But right now,

278
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:17,720
my mom is the one suffering the most,

279
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:20,040
dealing with debt and money problems.

280
00:21:20,120 --> 00:21:22,640
I want to talk to Pun,
but he won't talk to me.

281
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:24,600
I don't know what to do anymore.

282
00:21:26,200 --> 00:21:28,240
I really don't know what to do.

283
00:21:40,480 --> 00:21:42,080
My mom was right.

284
00:21:43,720 --> 00:21:46,080
She said if I heard all your reasons,

285
00:21:47,280 --> 00:21:49,800
I'd understand you and get less angry.

286
00:22:00,120 --> 00:22:01,800
So, what's next for you and Pun?

287
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:12,960
I don't think we can go on anymore.

288
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:21,120
I've asked Pun for a divorce,
but he won't agree.

289
00:22:27,360 --> 00:22:28,680
As for my mom's debt,

290
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:31,320
if he refuses to talk to me,

291
00:22:34,040 --> 00:22:36,840
I guess I'll have to let him
take the house.

292
00:22:54,360 --> 00:22:57,800
Why does the end of love
always have to be so bitter?

293
00:22:59,040 --> 00:23:00,600
Why couldn't you just talk it out?

294
00:23:02,120 --> 00:23:05,680
I want to talk,
but Pun refuses to speak with me.

295
00:23:11,360 --> 00:23:13,240
I know where he is right now.

296
00:23:15,080 --> 00:23:16,360
Do you want to talk to him?

297
00:23:24,960 --> 00:23:27,320
<i>Pun, I'm sorry.</i>

298
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:30,440
<i>I'll do anything now.</i>
<i>Please forgive me, Pun.</i>

299
00:23:32,080 --> 00:23:34,160
Read it, Pun!

300
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:36,880
Walking around like a mouse
caught in a trap, huh?

301
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:39,480
Did you do something wrong,

302
00:23:39,560 --> 00:23:41,400
or are you so restless,
you can't sit still?

303
00:23:41,480 --> 00:23:43,440
What are you babbling about?

304
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:45,080
Don't act innocent.

305
00:23:45,680 --> 00:23:48,280
I know everything about Pie and Win.

306
00:23:49,920 --> 00:23:51,720
If Win weren't her ex,

307
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:54,960
Pun would never know how many men
your daughter has been with.

308
00:23:55,600 --> 00:23:58,080
You said your daughter
has never had a boyfriend.

309
00:23:58,160 --> 00:24:01,160
You said you're so protective,
never letting her date any guy.

310
00:24:01,960 --> 00:24:03,760
Lying through your teeth.

311
00:24:05,200 --> 00:24:08,360
Don't look down on others
based on your own perspective.

312
00:24:08,440 --> 00:24:10,520
Everyone has their good and bad sides.

313
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:13,640
No matter how rich someone is,
they can still make mistakes.

314
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:15,720
Even your husband, for example.

315
00:24:17,120 --> 00:24:19,560
What does that have to do with Uncle?
Stop changing the subject.

316
00:24:19,640 --> 00:24:20,920
I'm not changing the subject.

317
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:22,400
This is the most relevant thing.

318
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:26,560
Oh, you're criticizing others
for hiding things and deceiving people.

319
00:24:26,640 --> 00:24:29,640
Why don't you ask your husband
what he's been hiding?

320
00:24:31,480 --> 00:24:32,560
What are you saying?

321
00:24:33,200 --> 00:24:34,360
What do you know?

322
00:24:35,560 --> 00:24:38,520
I really want to say it, but I can't.

323
00:24:38,600 --> 00:24:41,160
Because your son
has forced me not to speak.

324
00:24:41,240 --> 00:24:43,320
If you want to know, go ask him yourself.

325
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:45,680
But I'll tell you this.

326
00:24:45,760 --> 00:24:49,520
Your son and your husband
are teaming up to lie to you!

327
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:53,600
- Auntie.
- If you call me shameless,

328
00:24:53,680 --> 00:24:56,920
your son and husband
are just as shameless as I am.

329
00:25:18,160 --> 00:25:19,200
Yes, Mom?

330
00:25:19,280 --> 00:25:21,040
Are you hiding something from me?

331
00:25:21,760 --> 00:25:24,600
Pie's mother just told me to my face

332
00:25:24,680 --> 00:25:27,040
that you and your dad
are forcing her not to speak.

333
00:25:31,120 --> 00:25:32,360
It's nothing, Mom.

334
00:25:32,440 --> 00:25:34,000
I think she's just talking nonsense.

335
00:25:34,080 --> 00:25:36,040
I don't believe it's nothing.

336
00:25:36,120 --> 00:25:38,520
If you don't tell me,
I'll go ask your dad.

337
00:25:39,240 --> 00:25:40,080
<i>Mom.</i>

338
00:25:40,160 --> 00:25:41,480
Mom.

339
00:25:41,560 --> 00:25:42,520
Mom!

340
00:25:50,720 --> 00:25:52,240
No one's answering their phone.

341
00:25:53,160 --> 00:25:54,920
Hey, you!

342
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:56,840
Have you seen Pie? Where did she go?

343
00:25:56,920 --> 00:25:58,640
I don't know. I haven't seen her.

344
00:25:58,720 --> 00:26:00,960
But I saw Miss Krarok come by.

345
00:26:01,040 --> 00:26:02,800
So where is Krarok now?

346
00:26:02,880 --> 00:26:05,480
She's already gone.
You'll have to ask her yourself.

347
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:15,000
MOM

348
00:26:17,640 --> 00:26:19,840
Pun is at Uncle Dech's old house
right now.

349
00:26:19,920 --> 00:26:21,560
He's in a meeting
and will likely finish late.

350
00:26:23,480 --> 00:26:25,160
If you want to talk to him alone,

351
00:26:25,240 --> 00:26:26,840
you should go now.

352
00:26:38,920 --> 00:26:41,680
Seriously, why did you break up with Pie?

353
00:26:51,640 --> 00:26:53,320
It happened a long time ago.

354
00:26:53,400 --> 00:26:54,960
Forget it. I don't want to talk about it.

355
00:26:55,680 --> 00:26:57,720
The reason things are so messy right now

356
00:26:57,800 --> 00:27:00,320
is because both of you
are refusing to talk.

357
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:02,280
I don't know
what you guys are holding back.

358
00:27:05,840 --> 00:27:07,000
Just say it, Win.

359
00:27:07,080 --> 00:27:09,280
It's time to talk. Just say it.

360
00:27:14,160 --> 00:27:15,880
Pie's mom asked me to break up with her.

361
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:25,160
If her mom hadn't told you to break up,
would you have done it?

362
00:27:33,520 --> 00:27:34,760
Does she know, Win?

363
00:27:35,960 --> 00:27:39,440
Have you ever told her
that you didn't want to break up with her?

364
00:27:42,400 --> 00:27:44,480
It wouldn't have made a difference.

365
00:27:44,560 --> 00:27:46,520
It's easier for her
to see me as the bad guy.

366
00:27:47,200 --> 00:27:51,040
How did you feel when you found out
that Pun married Pie?

367
00:27:55,840 --> 00:27:58,520
Be honest, Win. No need to pretend.

368
00:27:58,600 --> 00:28:00,200
Just speak openly.

369
00:28:03,120 --> 00:28:04,400
I was sad, of course.

370
00:28:07,440 --> 00:28:08,760
But I'm happy

371
00:28:09,760 --> 00:28:11,520
that Pie chose Pun.

372
00:28:16,560 --> 00:28:20,560
Honestly, if I hadn't come back,
or I had died,

373
00:28:20,640 --> 00:28:22,560
she probably wouldn't have been troubled.

374
00:28:30,080 --> 00:28:32,000
That's how love works.

375
00:28:32,080 --> 00:28:35,400
Not everything goes the way we want it to.

376
00:28:35,480 --> 00:28:37,200
There are always twists.

377
00:28:37,280 --> 00:28:39,800
Unexpected things happen all the time.

378
00:28:40,680 --> 00:28:41,600
But it's up to us.

379
00:28:41,680 --> 00:28:45,960
We have to keep an open heart
and be ready to face surprises, Win.

380
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:48,520
Just like what happened with me.

381
00:29:01,400 --> 00:29:02,320
Rok.

382
00:29:03,880 --> 00:29:05,040
I'm sorry

383
00:29:06,280 --> 00:29:07,680
I didn't tell you the truth.

384
00:29:07,760 --> 00:29:09,840
Be angry with me, not Pie.

385
00:29:11,960 --> 00:29:13,560
I'm not mad at anyone.

386
00:29:16,640 --> 00:29:18,720
After hearing everyone's reasons,

387
00:29:20,360 --> 00:29:21,880
I understand.

388
00:29:23,920 --> 00:29:25,440
If I were Pie,

389
00:29:25,520 --> 00:29:29,200
I wouldn't know if I'd be brave enough
to tell my new boyfriend

390
00:29:29,280 --> 00:29:30,920
that I've been pregnant and miscarried.

391
00:29:34,760 --> 00:29:37,760
Some things, we just want to forget.

392
00:29:41,480 --> 00:29:42,480
Pie…

393
00:29:43,920 --> 00:29:45,920
She was pregnant and miscarried?

394
00:29:53,160 --> 00:29:54,440
Is that true, Rok?

395
00:29:56,560 --> 00:29:58,080
You didn't know that?

396
00:30:03,400 --> 00:30:05,760
- Where are you going, Win?!
- I'm going to see Pie.

397
00:30:06,440 --> 00:30:07,800
She's not at home.

398
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:10,240
Where is she then?

399
00:30:11,280 --> 00:30:12,240
Rok.

400
00:30:12,880 --> 00:30:15,480
Please tell me. I want to talk to her.

401
00:30:16,080 --> 00:30:17,280
Please, I'm begging you.

402
00:30:17,360 --> 00:30:20,000
Tell me where she is, please.

403
00:30:20,880 --> 00:30:22,400
She is on her way to Pun.

404
00:31:12,880 --> 00:31:14,760
DAD

405
00:31:19,240 --> 00:31:20,920
DAD

406
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:39,760
I want to pay off
all the debts for my mom.

407
00:31:40,480 --> 00:31:43,000
I'll sell the house, sell everything,

408
00:31:43,880 --> 00:31:46,440
and pay you back every penny.

409
00:31:47,680 --> 00:31:51,640
But the issue between us,
I don't want it to involve my mom.

410
00:31:54,480 --> 00:31:56,280
The issue between us, Pie?

411
00:31:58,600 --> 00:32:00,760
It's not just between us anymore.

412
00:32:01,560 --> 00:32:06,040
Because your mom
dragged both my dad and my mom into it.

413
00:32:06,680 --> 00:32:09,000
Your dad and mom?

414
00:32:10,200 --> 00:32:11,520
What do your parents have to do with this?

415
00:32:12,120 --> 00:32:13,480
What did you get my mom to do?

416
00:32:16,520 --> 00:32:18,360
There are many things you haven't told me.

417
00:32:19,480 --> 00:32:21,280
This is something
I don't need to tell you.

418
00:32:26,520 --> 00:32:27,480
Pun.

419
00:32:29,040 --> 00:32:31,200
Please, I'm begging you.

420
00:32:31,280 --> 00:32:32,840
I'm asking you directly.

421
00:32:33,480 --> 00:32:36,640
What do you want me to do
to make you happy?

422
00:32:37,840 --> 00:32:40,400
I know I've done wrong in the past,
I haven't been good,

423
00:32:41,280 --> 00:32:43,960
but I can't undo what's already been done.

424
00:32:45,640 --> 00:32:48,400
Right now, I'm willing to do anything.

425
00:32:48,480 --> 00:32:50,680
I'll do anything to end this here with me.

426
00:32:52,160 --> 00:32:54,640
I don't want anyone else
to get hurt because of this, Pun.

427
00:32:58,800 --> 00:33:00,800
You're saying
you're willing to do anything

428
00:33:02,200 --> 00:33:04,080
because you don't want this
to affect your mom, right?

429
00:33:04,760 --> 00:33:05,760
Yes.

430
00:33:08,000 --> 00:33:09,560
You love your mom so much

431
00:33:10,400 --> 00:33:12,360
that you're willing
to take everything on yourself.

432
00:33:12,440 --> 00:33:14,120
Are you sure you can handle it?

433
00:33:17,480 --> 00:33:18,560
If I can't handle it, I have to.

434
00:33:20,680 --> 00:33:22,320
Since I was born,

435
00:33:24,920 --> 00:33:27,240
my mom has had no one else
but me in her life,

436
00:33:28,200 --> 00:33:31,160
and my life has had no one else but her.

437
00:33:31,920 --> 00:33:33,680
No one else?

438
00:33:34,760 --> 00:33:36,960
No one else in your life, Pie?

439
00:33:37,040 --> 00:33:38,400
What about me, Pie?

440
00:33:38,480 --> 00:33:40,240
What about me?!

441
00:33:40,840 --> 00:33:42,400
Where do I stand in your life?

442
00:33:46,600 --> 00:33:47,920
Answer me!

443
00:33:56,360 --> 00:33:57,920
I'm asking you directly, Pie.

444
00:33:59,960 --> 00:34:01,960
All this time,

445
00:34:06,840 --> 00:34:08,840
have I ever been a part of your life?

446
00:34:13,080 --> 00:34:15,080
Did you ever love me?

447
00:34:24,520 --> 00:34:25,880
Why aren't you answering?

448
00:34:27,400 --> 00:34:29,560
Is it that hard to answer, Pie?

449
00:34:31,159 --> 00:34:32,400
Is it that hard to answer,

450
00:34:33,080 --> 00:34:34,880
or do you just not want to?

451
00:34:38,120 --> 00:34:40,320
Just say whether you love me or not.

452
00:34:42,159 --> 00:34:43,520
What's so hard about that?!

453
00:34:47,840 --> 00:34:49,120
Is it hard to answer

454
00:34:50,320 --> 00:34:52,480
because you never loved me?!

455
00:35:39,040 --> 00:35:40,240
Was this a setup?

456
00:35:40,960 --> 00:35:41,880
- No.
- No, it wasn't.

457
00:35:42,520 --> 00:35:43,480
Pie didn't know anything.

458
00:35:45,360 --> 00:35:46,560
Oh, I forgot.

459
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:49,400
I won't get the truth from you.

460
00:35:50,240 --> 00:35:51,320
Okay.

461
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:54,200
I know whatever I say,
you won't believe me anyway.

462
00:35:54,280 --> 00:35:55,240
That's right!

463
00:35:56,120 --> 00:35:57,240
I don't believe you!

464
00:35:57,320 --> 00:35:58,600
Hey, Pun!

465
00:35:58,680 --> 00:36:01,440
I came here to talk things out.
I don't want trouble.

466
00:36:02,640 --> 00:36:05,080
- Pun.
- You think I want trouble?

467
00:36:05,160 --> 00:36:06,160
Huh?

468
00:36:08,720 --> 00:36:09,760
Think about it.

469
00:36:10,760 --> 00:36:13,920
Two people I trust most in my life

470
00:36:15,240 --> 00:36:18,720
teaming up to hide things
and betraying me.

471
00:36:25,720 --> 00:36:28,200
Do you think I want to deal with this?

472
00:36:29,480 --> 00:36:31,400
It's my fault. It's all on me, Pun.

473
00:36:33,160 --> 00:36:36,760
If you're angry or disappointed,
it's because of me, no one else.

474
00:36:36,840 --> 00:36:38,120
Enough.

475
00:36:38,200 --> 00:36:39,920
Don't say anything more, Win.
Just go home.

476
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:40,960
I'm not leaving.

477
00:36:45,320 --> 00:36:48,320
The reason you have to go through all this
is because of fear.

478
00:36:50,680 --> 00:36:51,880
It's my fault.

479
00:36:52,720 --> 00:36:55,120
Because I wasn't brave enough
to protect you.

480
00:36:57,640 --> 00:36:59,600
I wasn't brave enough to confirm that…

481
00:37:01,320 --> 00:37:02,320
Confirm what?

482
00:37:07,280 --> 00:37:09,080
What are you trying to confirm?!

483
00:37:15,400 --> 00:37:16,920
Aren't you brave enough to speak up?

484
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:18,640
Why won't you say it?

485
00:37:18,720 --> 00:37:21,000
Someone like you is always too scared.

486
00:37:21,080 --> 00:37:23,440
You don't speak up.
When there's a problem, you run away.

487
00:37:23,520 --> 00:37:26,120
You refuse to face the truth
because you're a coward!

488
00:37:26,200 --> 00:37:27,640
I love Pie!

489
00:37:53,480 --> 00:37:55,920
There's never been a day
I haven't thought about her.

490
00:38:03,560 --> 00:38:05,800
The reason I went to school
and worked hard

491
00:38:06,960 --> 00:38:09,680
was to come back
as someone good enough for her.

492
00:38:15,880 --> 00:38:17,960
I regret leaving her.

493
00:38:21,800 --> 00:38:23,280
I regret that…

494
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:29,600
I regret not knowing…

495
00:38:30,720 --> 00:38:32,600
what bad things she had to go through.

496
00:38:35,760 --> 00:38:37,760
I want to protect her.

497
00:38:37,840 --> 00:38:39,840
I don't want her to be hurt again.

498
00:38:47,240 --> 00:38:48,680
Is this what you wanted to hear?

499
00:38:50,440 --> 00:38:52,040
I love Pie.

500
00:38:53,960 --> 00:38:56,960
If you want to kill me or ruin my life,

501
00:38:57,040 --> 00:38:59,320
go ahead and do it. Do it!

502
00:38:59,400 --> 00:39:01,960
- You want to die, don't you?!
- Pun!

503
00:39:02,040 --> 00:39:04,600
- You really want to die, huh?
- Pun!

504
00:39:05,480 --> 00:39:07,960
Pun! Stop!

505
00:39:08,040 --> 00:39:09,920
- Listen! Stop!
- I won't stop! What?!

506
00:39:10,000 --> 00:39:10,960
What happens if I don't stop?

507
00:39:11,040 --> 00:39:12,840
Are you that worried about him?

508
00:39:15,560 --> 00:39:17,680
Pun, don't! Stop!

509
00:39:17,760 --> 00:39:19,120
Stop! That's enough!

510
00:39:19,200 --> 00:39:21,480
- I won't stop!
- Enough, Pun!

511
00:39:22,320 --> 00:39:24,800
You know I worry about others
more than myself.

512
00:39:24,880 --> 00:39:26,240
Pun, please stop!

513
00:39:29,320 --> 00:39:30,840
Damn it! Let go!

514
00:40:32,600 --> 00:40:35,120
- Pie!
- Pie!

515
00:40:35,200 --> 00:40:38,960
- Pie!
- Pie!

516
00:40:39,680 --> 00:40:40,720
Pie!

517
00:40:45,920 --> 00:40:47,040
Pie!

518
00:41:06,080 --> 00:41:07,000
Stop!

519
00:41:08,160 --> 00:41:09,320
Don't touch her yet.

520
00:41:10,440 --> 00:41:12,680
Don't move her right now. It's dangerous.

521
00:41:13,760 --> 00:41:15,400
I'll call an ambulance first.

522
00:41:46,440 --> 00:41:47,560
One family member only.

523
00:41:50,840 --> 00:41:52,200
My brother here is her husband.

524
00:41:54,760 --> 00:41:56,240
Then you can sit in the front.

525
00:41:58,960 --> 00:42:00,640
Can I sit with the patient?

526
00:42:00,720 --> 00:42:02,040
Yes, of course. Go ahead.

527
00:42:13,320 --> 00:42:14,800
The patient has lost a lot of blood.

528
00:42:14,880 --> 00:42:18,800
Oxygen levels are low.
10L Mask with Bag and 1,000 ml saline.

529
00:42:50,600 --> 00:42:51,560
EMERGENCY

530
00:43:00,800 --> 00:43:03,280
The patient fell down the stairs,
lost blood, and has low blood pressure.

531
00:43:33,240 --> 00:43:34,800
Are you a family member
of Phitpicha Attwijit?

532
00:43:34,880 --> 00:43:35,840
Yes.

533
00:43:36,360 --> 00:43:38,840
I'm her husband. How is my wife?

534
00:43:39,600 --> 00:43:41,000
The patient is in shock.

535
00:43:41,080 --> 00:43:43,120
She's lost a lot of blood
from a head injury.

536
00:43:43,200 --> 00:43:44,680
Her blood pressure dropped,

537
00:43:44,760 --> 00:43:48,920
but we've administered fluids,
and her pressure is now stable.

538
00:43:49,680 --> 00:43:51,560
The head wound is quite deep,

539
00:43:51,640 --> 00:43:53,960
but we've stitched it up.

540
00:43:54,040 --> 00:43:56,760
As for the ankle,

541
00:43:56,840 --> 00:43:58,720
we've done an X-ray,
and there are no broken bones.

542
00:43:59,640 --> 00:44:00,800
It looks like a sprained ligament.

543
00:44:01,600 --> 00:44:03,240
As for the brain X-ray,

544
00:44:03,320 --> 00:44:07,760
I believe the patient has a skull fracture
with bleeding above the right dura mater.

545
00:44:07,840 --> 00:44:09,480
From what I've examined,

546
00:44:09,560 --> 00:44:12,000
the patient is unconscious
and not responding to commands.

547
00:44:12,720 --> 00:44:14,760
The left side of her body isn't moving.

548
00:44:14,840 --> 00:44:16,920
We need to perform surgery immediately
to drain the blood.

549
00:44:19,080 --> 00:44:19,960
Surgery?

550
00:44:22,440 --> 00:44:24,520
Will my wife be safe?

551
00:44:26,080 --> 00:44:27,560
I can't say for sure yet.

552
00:44:27,640 --> 00:44:29,520
We'll have to wait and see
after the surgery.

553
00:44:30,080 --> 00:44:32,000
Well, the current treatment plan

554
00:44:32,080 --> 00:44:35,320
is to perform the surgery
to save the patient's life.

555
00:44:35,400 --> 00:44:38,360
But I must say it's quite risky.

556
00:44:38,440 --> 00:44:41,120
There's a chance the patient
could die during surgery,

557
00:44:41,200 --> 00:44:42,920
or even if she survives,

558
00:44:43,520 --> 00:44:46,600
she might not wake up
and could fall into a coma.

559
00:44:46,680 --> 00:44:49,440
She could also end up
permanently disabled.

560
00:45:08,440 --> 00:45:09,800
Doctor, is it…

561
00:45:10,920 --> 00:45:12,000
Is surgery

562
00:45:13,720 --> 00:45:15,400
the best option?

563
00:45:17,320 --> 00:45:19,360
At this point, yes.

564
00:45:21,400 --> 00:45:22,600
Then, let's do it.

565
00:45:47,760 --> 00:45:48,840
<i>Is there anything I can help with?</i>

566
00:45:49,880 --> 00:45:50,920
Coming through.

567
00:45:53,640 --> 00:45:54,440
All done.

568
00:45:56,440 --> 00:45:57,800
<i>So you've never brought a guy before?</i>

569
00:45:59,200 --> 00:46:02,800
Then I must be someone special.

570
00:46:12,560 --> 00:46:15,320
<i>If you aren't tired of my indecisiveness</i>

571
00:46:15,920 --> 00:46:17,720
<i>and aren't exhausted</i>
<i>from taking care of me,</i>

572
00:46:18,760 --> 00:46:20,680
then yes.

573
00:46:21,240 --> 00:46:22,640
Yes!

574
00:46:54,400 --> 00:46:56,040
<i>I had a relationship with a guy.</i>

575
00:46:56,640 --> 00:46:58,280
<i>That guy is…</i>

576
00:46:59,360 --> 00:47:00,520
Win.

577
00:47:02,720 --> 00:47:05,560
I was pregnant, but I miscarried
because of an accident.

578
00:47:16,360 --> 00:47:17,160
Let go!

579
00:47:38,360 --> 00:47:40,080
Alright, that works.

580
00:47:48,000 --> 00:47:48,960
Rok!

581
00:47:49,040 --> 00:47:50,720
- Auntie.
- Rok!

582
00:47:51,400 --> 00:47:52,400
Where is Pie?

583
00:47:54,160 --> 00:47:55,120
You know, right?

584
00:47:55,800 --> 00:47:57,440
Don't side with Pie.

585
00:47:57,520 --> 00:47:59,040
Don't help her hide the truth.

586
00:47:59,120 --> 00:48:00,960
Tell me now. Where is she? Don't lie.

587
00:48:01,040 --> 00:48:02,200
Wait, Ms. Tubtim!

588
00:48:02,840 --> 00:48:05,320
Take it easy.
You don't have to pressure her.

589
00:48:05,400 --> 00:48:07,400
If I don't pressure her,
it'll just be another problem.

590
00:48:07,480 --> 00:48:09,040
Isn't the issue today

591
00:48:09,120 --> 00:48:12,240
because Pie and Rok teamed up
to lie about Mae Hong Son?

592
00:48:12,840 --> 00:48:14,800
If your kid hadn't helped Pie lie,

593
00:48:14,880 --> 00:48:16,760
she wouldn't be going through
all these troubles

594
00:48:16,840 --> 00:48:18,280
haunting her now!

595
00:48:18,360 --> 00:48:20,720
Hey, hold on.

596
00:48:20,800 --> 00:48:22,480
How can you blame my kid?

597
00:48:22,560 --> 00:48:24,080
I'm not blaming just Rok.

598
00:48:24,160 --> 00:48:25,280
I'm blaming Pie too.

599
00:48:25,360 --> 00:48:26,960
These two teamed up to lie.

600
00:48:27,040 --> 00:48:28,720
What about blaming yourself?

601
00:48:28,800 --> 00:48:30,960
What kind of mother are you
that your child can't even tell the truth?

602
00:48:31,040 --> 00:48:32,560
Your child have to team up
with a friend to lie.

603
00:48:32,640 --> 00:48:35,760
If you can't be a safe space
for your child, don't blame others!

604
00:48:35,840 --> 00:48:37,280
You think I'm a bad person.

605
00:48:37,360 --> 00:48:38,320
What about you?

606
00:48:38,400 --> 00:48:41,000
How did you raise your child
to help a friend lie?

607
00:48:41,080 --> 00:48:42,440
Your child lied to me!

608
00:48:42,520 --> 00:48:43,800
Hey!

609
00:48:43,880 --> 00:48:46,680
Don't look down on us.
Our family has never exploited our child.

610
00:48:46,760 --> 00:48:49,880
We've never used our child's love
to fulfill our own needs,

611
00:48:49,960 --> 00:48:52,760
causing our child's life
to be chaotic like yours.

612
00:48:52,840 --> 00:48:53,920
What?

613
00:48:54,000 --> 00:48:55,720
I've never taken advantage of my child.

614
00:48:55,800 --> 00:48:57,320
I've only given Pie the best.

615
00:48:58,200 --> 00:48:59,760
Ask yourself!

616
00:48:59,840 --> 00:49:02,640
Is what you're doing for Pie
or for yourself?

617
00:49:03,320 --> 00:49:04,800
What? You've gone too far now!

618
00:49:04,880 --> 00:49:06,400
It's still not enough!

619
00:49:06,480 --> 00:49:08,880
Out of respect for Pie's friendship,
I don't want to be harsh.

620
00:49:08,960 --> 00:49:10,600
You're a mother, and so am I.

621
00:49:10,680 --> 00:49:13,760
We love our children,
and we know they love us, but sometimes…

622
00:49:14,640 --> 00:49:15,760
Sometimes,

623
00:49:15,840 --> 00:49:18,760
we take advantage of our children's love
without realizing it.

624
00:49:18,840 --> 00:49:20,960
I'm just warning you,
in case you wake up to it!

625
00:49:21,680 --> 00:49:22,640
What is this?

626
00:49:22,720 --> 00:49:24,040
Why are you suddenly attacking me?

627
00:49:24,120 --> 00:49:26,000
Are you so perfect
that you raise your child like this?

628
00:49:26,080 --> 00:49:28,080
I raise my child better than you do.
How do you raise your child?

629
00:49:28,160 --> 00:49:29,400
- What did you say?
- You started this!

630
00:49:29,480 --> 00:49:32,960
- Are you really that great?
- Take care of your own child first.

631
00:49:33,040 --> 00:49:34,360
- What's your problem?
- Stop!

632
00:49:37,360 --> 00:49:39,600
Let's talk, just the two of us. Come on.

633
00:49:41,840 --> 00:49:43,040
Let's go!

634
00:49:44,120 --> 00:49:45,600
- She needs a lesson!
- Calm down.

635
00:49:45,680 --> 00:49:46,880
You shouldn't have stopped me.

636
00:49:46,960 --> 00:49:48,680
Hey.

637
00:49:48,760 --> 00:49:50,680
Your heart is racing.
It's pounding like crazy.

638
00:49:50,760 --> 00:49:52,560
I'm angry. How dare
she talk about Rok like that?

639
00:49:53,280 --> 00:49:56,080
- I'm exhausted, Dad. I really am.
- Careful with your ankle.

640
00:49:56,160 --> 00:49:58,360
Rok. Let go!

641
00:49:58,440 --> 00:49:59,640
What's wrong with your mom?

642
00:49:59,720 --> 00:50:02,680
Has she lost her mind yelling at me?
I won't accept this, Rok.

643
00:50:02,760 --> 00:50:04,720
I know the truth now.

644
00:50:04,800 --> 00:50:07,040
I've told my parents everything.

645
00:50:07,720 --> 00:50:10,000
What do you know? What did you say?

646
00:50:11,800 --> 00:50:13,880
Don't accuse me of interfering.

647
00:50:13,960 --> 00:50:15,480
But today,

648
00:50:15,560 --> 00:50:18,280
I'm going to speak frankly
as Pie's close friend.

649
00:50:19,920 --> 00:50:21,320
Auntie.

650
00:50:21,960 --> 00:50:23,560
Pie loves you very much.

651
00:50:24,200 --> 00:50:26,320
Whenever you told her to do something,
even if she didn't want to,

652
00:50:26,400 --> 00:50:27,920
she did it all for you.

653
00:50:28,560 --> 00:50:31,640
She never complained or said anything
because she loves you.

654
00:50:33,320 --> 00:50:36,200
But you've used her love against her,

655
00:50:36,280 --> 00:50:38,200
taking advantage of it in every way.

656
00:50:38,280 --> 00:50:40,040
I've never taken advantage of my child.

657
00:50:40,120 --> 00:50:42,440
What I asked Pie to do
was for her own good.

658
00:50:42,520 --> 00:50:45,240
For her own good or for yours, Auntie?

659
00:50:50,120 --> 00:50:51,560
I've known her for a long time.

660
00:50:53,080 --> 00:50:55,280
She's someone who always
looks on the bright side,

661
00:50:55,360 --> 00:50:57,120
someone who enjoys life.

662
00:50:57,880 --> 00:51:00,080
She's the energy booster
for all her friends.

663
00:51:01,200 --> 00:51:02,320
But today,

664
00:51:03,200 --> 00:51:05,320
she doesn't even have the energy

665
00:51:05,960 --> 00:51:08,000
to hold herself up, Auntie.

666
00:51:12,000 --> 00:51:14,440
You know Pie loves you
and is willing to do anything,

667
00:51:15,120 --> 00:51:17,040
so you take her for granted.

668
00:51:18,160 --> 00:51:23,880
You've made her do what you want
without ever asking what she really wants.

669
00:51:25,400 --> 00:51:27,040
Have you ever known

670
00:51:28,640 --> 00:51:31,200
what she has sacrificed for you?

671
00:51:40,000 --> 00:51:41,480
She hid the truth about Win.

672
00:51:42,080 --> 00:51:44,120
She endured being with Pun's family.

673
00:51:44,840 --> 00:51:48,080
She forced herself not to divorce Pun,
even though she was unhappy.

674
00:51:48,800 --> 00:51:50,240
And today,

675
00:51:50,320 --> 00:51:53,920
she's going to Pun because of your debts.

676
00:51:59,760 --> 00:52:01,720
She has done everything
for you her whole life.

677
00:52:04,200 --> 00:52:08,160
And you still have the nerve to say
you've never taken advantage of her?

678
00:52:16,400 --> 00:52:17,440
Auntie.

679
00:52:19,880 --> 00:52:22,800
When was the last time you saw her happy?

680
00:52:34,520 --> 00:52:35,880
If you really cared,

681
00:52:37,080 --> 00:52:40,600
you'd know that she hasn't been happy
for a long time.

682
00:52:47,440 --> 00:52:49,600
I feel sorry for Pie.

683
00:52:49,680 --> 00:52:52,040
I feel sorry for my best friend.

684
00:52:54,120 --> 00:52:57,840
And I want my best friend back.

685
00:52:59,440 --> 00:53:01,160
The friend who supported everyone,

686
00:53:01,240 --> 00:53:03,520
the friend who enjoyed life.

687
00:53:06,800 --> 00:53:09,400
The one who can bring her back to herself

688
00:53:11,280 --> 00:53:12,680
is you, Auntie.

689
00:53:27,920 --> 00:53:31,360
PUN

690
00:53:33,800 --> 00:53:36,360
Pun, Pie is with you, right?

691
00:53:39,360 --> 00:53:40,440
What?

692
00:53:41,200 --> 00:53:42,680
Pie is in the hospital?

693
00:53:44,800 --> 00:53:46,040
Pie…

694
00:53:55,240 --> 00:53:58,040
KDMS ORTHOPEDIC HOSPITAL

695
00:54:07,840 --> 00:54:10,040
Excuse me. Which way
to the operating room?

696
00:54:10,120 --> 00:54:13,120
Take a left, then take
the elevator to the third floor.

697
00:54:13,200 --> 00:54:14,880
- Okay. Let's go.
- Thank you.

698
00:54:22,480 --> 00:54:24,280
Did she fall down the stairs?

699
00:54:24,360 --> 00:54:26,960
Is this an accident, or…

700
00:54:30,520 --> 00:54:31,960
I didn't mean to.

701
00:54:33,480 --> 00:54:35,800
You didn't do this
out of anger towards me, did you?

702
00:54:39,160 --> 00:54:40,400
No, I didn't.

703
00:54:41,480 --> 00:54:43,200
Win was with you, right?

704
00:54:48,680 --> 00:54:53,040
It must be karma, my dear Pie.

705
00:54:53,120 --> 00:54:54,320
Auntie.

706
00:55:00,240 --> 00:55:01,240
Pun.

707
00:55:03,320 --> 00:55:05,200
I'm sorry.

708
00:55:05,280 --> 00:55:07,440
I was the one who forced her
to hide the truth.

709
00:55:07,520 --> 00:55:09,760
It's my fault, Pun.

710
00:55:09,840 --> 00:55:11,920
I made her go through this.

711
00:55:12,000 --> 00:55:13,720
Please don't hate or be angry with Pie.

712
00:55:13,800 --> 00:55:15,920
If you're going to hate someone, hate me.

713
00:55:16,000 --> 00:55:17,920
Please. I'm sorry.

714
00:57:05,960 --> 00:57:06,800
Doctor.

715
00:57:07,400 --> 00:57:08,440
How is Pie?

716
00:57:08,520 --> 00:57:11,600
We removed the blood clot
from the meninges.

717
00:57:11,680 --> 00:57:15,080
There were no complications
during the surgery.

718
00:57:15,160 --> 00:57:16,680
As for the ankle,

719
00:57:16,760 --> 00:57:19,160
the orthopedic doctor
has taken care of it.

720
00:57:19,240 --> 00:57:21,280
However, the patient is still unconscious.

721
00:57:21,360 --> 00:57:24,160
We'll need to assess her condition again
after the surgery.

722
00:57:24,920 --> 00:57:26,920
We'll be transferring her to the ICU now.

723
00:57:27,000 --> 00:57:30,480
If anything changes,
we'll inform the family right away.

724
00:57:31,840 --> 00:57:33,040
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

725
00:58:16,040 --> 00:58:18,240
Our love can't go on anymore.

726
00:58:18,320 --> 00:58:19,120
Let's get a divorce.

727
00:58:19,200 --> 00:58:20,760
I'll never divorce him!

728
00:58:20,840 --> 00:58:23,400
Never! Do you hear me?
I won't divorce him!

729
00:58:23,480 --> 00:58:25,600
- Just get a divorce.
- No!

730
00:58:25,680 --> 00:58:28,200
Why should I divorce
so those two can be happy?

731
00:58:28,280 --> 00:58:30,760
Don't be the third party
between Pun and Pie.

732
00:58:30,840 --> 00:58:32,280
It's not good.

733
00:58:32,360 --> 00:58:33,680
Look at Aunt Nhun. Do you see?

734
00:58:34,640 --> 00:58:37,400
Someone who's been through this
can never truly be happy.

735
00:58:39,840 --> 00:58:41,160
Nurse!

736
00:58:41,240 --> 00:58:42,320
My wife is awake!

737
00:58:42,400 --> 00:58:45,280
Pun, what happened that day?

738
00:58:45,360 --> 00:58:47,400
Can you tell me?

739
00:59:14,360 --> 00:59:17,120
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
